>>>>>>> Diabetes UK are calling for an end to the use of terms such as
'diabetic' or 'suitable for diabetics' on food labels.
>>>>>>> This position statement is intended to help people with diabetes make
more informed choices when buying foods, and to encourage manufacturers and
>>>>>>> Diabetes UK and the European Commission (EC) have concluded that there
is no role or benefit from the use of diabetic foods. Diabetes UK will
continue to work on influencing manufacturers and retailers to ensure that
consumers are not misled by labelling food as diabetic or suitable for
